==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Taeniosomi
<hw>Tae`ni*o*so"mi</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>taini`a</grk> ribbon + <grk>sw^ma</grk> body.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An order of fishes remarkable for their long and
compressed form. The ribbon fishes are examples. See <cref>Ribbon
fish</cref>, under <er>Ribbon</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

